div.p:
I Thank you for your letter. I earnestly desire your proficiency and comfort in the good ways of God
                     ▪ A christian must be humble but never discouraged. The first is a duty; the second is a sin. Though the bare talking of the lips tends only to penury;


yet talking of God, and of the things of God, from the heart, is part of the christian practice, especially among those that are endued with a sense of religion. Our words must be savoury, seasoned with salt; tending to edification; and such as may minister grace to the hearers.
